        "created_at": "2025-03-16T01:59:49.163Z",
        "cooked": "<p>The only setting influencing font size I found is <code>File</code> &gt; <code>Preferences</code> &gt; <code>Appearance</code> &gt; <code>Zoom level</code>, which seems to set UI sizing in general, and gives a dropdown with only 5 predetermined options.</p>\n<p>Personally I find this very limiting, and I’d like a separate setting for font size. It’s supported in similar Apps (see for example Element), and would allow me to precisely set whichever size I find most readable, without also increasing the space taken up by other UI elements, profile pictures, and so on.</p>\n<p>Additionally, I would enjoy making this setting available through the usual keyboard shortcuts:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>Ctrl</code> <code>+</code> or  <code>Ctrl</code> <code>scroll up</code>: increase size</li>\n<li><code>Ctrl</code> <code>-</code> or <code>Ctrl</code> <code>scroll down</code>: decrease size</li>\n<li><code>Ctrl</code> <code>0</code>: return to 100% size</li>\n</ul>\n<p>These would work alright for me if they controlled UI scaling in general (as long as they work in smaller increments than 25%), but for the same reasons as above, I’d prefer adjusting font size instead.</p>\n<p>Thanks!</p>",
