        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"goth-turtle\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"67729\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/goth-turtle/48/51184_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> goth-turtle:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Additionally, I would enjoy making this setting available through the usual keyboard shortcuts:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>Ctrl</code> <code>+</code> or <code>Ctrl</code> <code>scroll up</code>: increase size</li>\n<li><code>Ctrl</code> <code>-</code> or <code>Ctrl</code> <code>scroll down</code>: decrease size</li>\n<li><code>Ctrl</code> <code>0</code>: return to 100% size</li>\n</ul>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>These shortcuts already exist (needs to be the <kbd>+</kbd>/<kbd>-</kbd>/<kbd>0</kbd> in the top row and not the num pad though). They are also under the <code>View</code> menu.</p>",
